quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  26,10,"And when thy Lord called to Moses, 'Go to the people of the evildoers"
  26,11,the people of Pharaoh; will they not be godfearing
  26,12,"He said, 'My Lord, I fear they will cry me lies"
  26,13,"and my breast will be straitened, and my tongue will not be loosed; so send to Aaron"
  26,14,"They also have a sin against me, and I fear they will slay me"
  26,15,"Said He, 'No indeed; but go, both of you, with Our signs, and We assuredly shall be with you, listening"
  26,16,"So go you to Pharaoh, and say, \"Verily, I am the Messenger of the Lord of all Being"
  26,17,so send forth with us the Children of Israel
  26,18,"He said, 'Did we not raise thee amongst us as a child? Didst thou not tarry among us years of thy life"
  26,19,"And thou didst the deed thou didst, being one of the ungrateful"
  26,20,"Said he, 'Indeed I did it then, being one of those that stray"
  26,21,"so I fled from you, fearing you. But my Lord gave me Judgment and made me one of the Envoys"
  26,22,"That is a blessing thou reproachest me with, having enslaved the Children of Israel"
  26,23,"Pharaoh said, 'And what is the Lord of all Being"
  26,24,"He said, 'The Lord of the heavens and earth, and what between them is, if you have faith"
  26,25,"Said he to those about him, 'Do you not hear"
  26,26,"He said, 'Your Lord and the Lord of your fathers, the ancients"
  26,27,"Said he, 'Surely your Messenger who was sent to you is possessed"
  26,28,"He said, 'The Lord of the East and West, and what between them is, if you have understanding"
  26,29,"Said he, 'If thou takest a god other than me, I shall surely make thee one of the imprisoned"
  26,30,"He said, 'What, even though I brought thee something so manifest"
  26,31,"Said he, 'Bring it then, if thou art of the truthful"
  26,32,"So he cast his staff, and behold, it was a serpent manifest"
  26,33,"And he drew forth his hand, and lo, it was white to the beholders"